Inga edulis

   [1260.jpg]
   Authority Mart.
   Family Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Fabales:Leguminosae
   Synonyms
   Common names food inga, ice cream bean, pois sucre, guarna, guamo,
   guama, guaba, huaba, inga, guamo bejuco, chalaite, rabo de mico, pacay,
   ingá cipó, inga de metro
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 1260

   Notes
   SOURCES
   Duke J 1981 pp 101-102 [DRA, RAIN, TEMP, PH]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 218 [USE]
   Vietmeyer N 1989 pp 277-285 [USE, KTMP, PHO, RAIN, TEMP, PH, DRA, TEXT]
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial tree. Flowers in February-May and fruit several months later.
   COMMON NAMES
   Ice-cream bean, Guava machete, Inga cipo, Guavobejuco, Guava.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonyms: I. tropica, I. vaga. Ice-cream bean is native of
   Central and South America. It can be found at elevations between sea
   level and 2200 m. It can grow up to 17 m tall. Extensively used for
   shade of coffee, tea, and cacao, especially in Central America.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
